  m_Name: Pes_Distal_Phalanx_D4_L
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::ModelPartDataSO
  id: Pes_Distal_Phalanx_D4_L
  partName: Pes Distal Phalanx D4 Left
  descriptionChunks:
  - The left distal phalanx of the fourth hind digit is the terminal bone supporting
    the claw within the canine hindpaw. This structure contributes to traction, toe
    stability, and coordinated locomotion during walking and running activities.
    Tendons attached to the distal phalanx control digital movement while maintaining
    proper alignment and balance throughout the hindpaw.
  - The fourth digit also assists with distributing mechanical forces and maintaining
    stable ground contact during movement. Proper structural integrity is essential
    for efficient paw mechanics and locomotor performance.
